The evidence with the title 'Khrushchev's son: giving crimea back to Russia not an option ' says Mar 6, 2014  ... Khrushchev 's son Sergei says Crimea was given to Ukraine in 1954 for economic reasons , and that he never heard that Russia's president wanted it  ... For centuries , Crimea was part of Russia , until 1954 when Soviet leader Nikita Khrushchev gave the peninsula to Ukraine - at that time a Soviet republic . 
